{
  "texts": [
    "This map corresponds with the overlay map, which shares the objective of representing term density.",
    "Points on the map become increasingly yellow as the aggregation of terms intensifies and as the significance of adjacent terms rises.",
    "The core area of the visualization accentuates terms that are predominantly used in GeoGebra-centric research, including \"functions\", \"geometry\", \"mathematics\", \"problem solving\", \"students\", \"dynamic mathematics software\", \"visualization\", \"mathematics education\", \"dynamic geometry software\" and \"calculus\".",
    "www.richtmann.org Vol 15 No 1 January 2025 140 6.2 Thematic Clusters Three main clusters were identified based on the most frequently occurring words, illustrated in blue, green, and red and yellow, see Figure 5.",
    "The first cluster, illustrated in blue, centers around the use of GeoGebra as an interactive geometry learning tool."
  ]
}